### Overview

This is a simple Discord.js v14 bot that implements a single slash command, **`/ban`**. The command takes a user ID as an argument and bans the user from the server.

### Requirements

- **Node.js**: Version 16.13.0 or later
- **Discord.js**: Version 14.0.0 or later

### Installation

1. **Clone the Repository**:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/Ankit-Rajput/discord-bot-ban.git
   ```

2. **Install Dependencies**:
   ```bash
   cd discord-bot-ban
   npm install
   ```

### Usage

1. **Start the Bot**:
   ```bash
   npm start
   ```

### Command Structure

- **Command Name**: `/ban`
- **Command Description**: Bans a user from the server
- **Command Usage**: `/ban <user ID>`

### Command Functionality

- **User Input**: The command takes a user ID as an argument.
- **Bot Response**: The bot responds with a confirmation message indicating that the user has been banned.

### Code

```javascript
// Import the Discord.js modules
const { Client, GatewayIntentBits, Partials, Collection } = require("discord.js");

// Create a new Discord client
const client = new Client({
  intents: [GatewayIntentBits.Guilds, GatewayIntentBits.GuildMessages],
  partials: [Partials.Message, Partials.Channel],
});

// Define the slash command
const banCommand = {
  name: "ban",
  description: "Bans a user from the server",
  options: [
    {
      name: "user_id",
      description: "The user ID to ban",
      type: "STRING",
      required: true,
    },
  ],
};

// Create a collection to store the slash commands
const commands = new Collection();

// Add the ban command to the collection
commands.set(banCommand.name, banCommand);

// Define the event listener for the interactionCreate event
client.on("interactionCreate", async (interaction) => {
  // Check if the interaction is a slash command
  if (!interaction.isCommand()) return;

  // Get the command name
  const commandName = interaction.commandName;

  // Check if the command exists
  if (!commands.has(commandName)) return;

  // Get the command options
  const command = commands.get(commandName);
  const options = interaction.options.data;

  // Check if the command has options
  if (command.options.length > 0) {
    // Get the user ID from the options
    const userId = options[0].value;

    // Ban the user
    await interaction.guild.members.ban(userId);

    // Send a confirmation message
    await interaction.reply({
      content: `User with ID ${userId} has been banned from the server.`,
      ephemeral: true,
    });
  } else {
    // Send an error message
    await interaction.reply({
      content: "Invalid command usage. Please provide a user ID.",
      ephemeral: true,
    });
  }
});

// Login to Discord with the bot token
client.login(process.env.BOT_TOKEN);
```

