### When to Use `==` and `.equals()`

Now that you know the difference between comparing strings using `==` and `.equals()`, you might be wondering when to use each method. Here are some general guidelines:

- Use `==` when you want to compare the references of two objects. This is useful when you want to check whether two objects are the same object in memory.
- Use `.equals()` when you want to compare the values of two objects. This is useful when you want to check whether two objects have the same value.

### Conclusion

